Rene Pawlowitz, AKA Shed, has today released a double-EP under his Head High alias. 

Since 2010 Pawlowitz has reserved the Head High name for rave-fuelled, thumping techno. Titled Megatrap, the eight-track record arrived on the shelves at Berlin record store Hard Wax today. (Hard Wax are calling it an EP, not an album.) 

Megatrap contains an "XXX Mono Mix" of 2010's piano house anthem "It's A Love Thing," along with seven other unreleased cuts. It's available on both vinyl and digital formats via Pawlowitz's Power House label. You can listen to soundclips over at Hard Wax.
